---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
---

<Layout title="Example Reconstruction | Prima Veritas">

<main class="flex-1">

  <PageHero
    title="Example Reconstruction"
    subtitle="A concrete example of how fragmented operational history becomes a sealed, reproducible sequence."
  />

  <Section title="Scenario">
    <p>
      A set of operational logs tracks updates to an order across multiple systems: an order
      management system, a customer support dashboard, and a fulfillment or shipping tool.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each system records events independently. Timestamps drift. Field formats differ.
      Identifiers are inconsistent. No single system preserves the full history.
    </p>
    <p>
      The result is a fragmented view of what actually happened.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <!-- RAW INTAKE — bare for grid layout -->
  <Section title="Raw Intake" bare>
    <div class="mt-6 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-w-5xl text-sm text-off-white/80">

      <div>
        <strong>Order System</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          14:02:11 ORDER_7421 → CREATED<br/>
          14:05:33 ADDRESS UPDATED
        </code>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Support Log</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          Ticket opened for order 7421<br/>
          Customer requested delivery change
        </code>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Fulfillment Record</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          Shipment scheduled<br/>
          Delivery attempt recorded
        </code>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80">
      <strong>Observed Issues</strong>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-off-white/60">
        <li>Timestamp drift</li>
        <li>Non-uniform identifiers (ORDER_7421 vs 7421 vs free text)</li>
        <li>Missing cross-reference keys</li>
        <li>Events spread across unrelated systems</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Canonical Envelope Normalization">
    <p>
      Each raw record is transformed into a canonical structure with a unified timestamp,
      source identifier, schema version, and structured payload.
    </p>
    <code class="block mt-4 text-off-white/60">
{`{
  event_id: "e1032",
  source: "order.system",
  timestamp: "2026-04-12T14:02:11Z",
  payload: { order_id: "7421", status: "CREATED" }
}`}
    </code>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Event Chain Construction">
    <p>
      Each event is hashed. The hash of the prior event is embedded in the next.
      Order is explicit.
    </p>
    <p>
      Any change to the sequence breaks its integrity.
    </p>
    <code class="block mt-4 text-off-white/60">
{`e1032 → hash: a94f...
e1033 → prev_hash: a94f...
e1034 → prev_hash: b221...`}
    </code>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Deterministic Reconstruction">
    <p>
      From the ordered sequence, system state at any point in time can be reconstructed.
    </p>
    <p>
      Order creation, address changes, support intervention, and delivery attempts are
      derived from a single unified history.
    </p>
    <p>
      Given the same input, reconstruction output is identical across environments.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Independent Verification">
    <p>
      The final output contains the full event sequence along with its integrity structure.
    </p>
    <p>
      A third party can verify that the sequence is complete, ordered, and unchanged —
      without access to the original systems.
    </p>
    <p>
      If any part of the sequence has been altered, the verification result will not match.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <!-- GENERATE ARTIFACT — stays raw due to JS and complex layout -->
  <section class="border-b border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">

      <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
        Generate a Verified Record
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80">
        Upload a CSV to reconstruct and verify a complete event history.
      </p>

      <!-- UPLOAD -->
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-6">

        <label class="bg-charcoal border border-white/10 text-off-white text-sm px-4 py-2 cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">
          Select CSV File
          <input type="file" accept=".csv" class="hidden" />
        </label>

        <button id="generate-btn"
          class="bg-carbon-navy font-semibold text-sm border border-white/20 px-4 py-2 min-w-[180px] flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
          <span id="btn-text">Generate Artifact</span>
          <span id="btn-spinner" class="hidden w-4 h-4 border-2 border-white/40 border-t-white rounded-full animate-spin"></span>
        </button>

        <a href="/sample.csv" download
          class="nav-link text-sm opacity-75 hover:text-[var(--accent)]">
          Download Sample CSV →
        </a>

      </div>

      <div id="status-message" class="text-sm min-h-[1.25rem] opacity-0"></div>

      <!-- SUCCESS STATE -->
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <div id="result"
          class="mt-6 border border-white/10 p-6 text-sm text-off-white/80 hidden">
          <p class="text-off-white font-semibold mb-2">Artifact Generated Successfully</p>
          <p class="text-off-white/70 mb-4">
            Artifact generated successfully. Your dataset has been reconstructed into a deterministic event sequence.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6 text-off-white/60 space-y-4">
            <div>
              <div>Artifact Hash</div>
              <div id="artifact-hash" class="font-mono break-all">—</div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <div>Event Count</div>
              <div id="event-count" class="font-mono">—</div>
            </div>

            <div id="preview-section" class="mt-6 hidden">
              <div class="text-off-white mb-2">Preview of reconstructed events</div>
              <pre id="preview-content" class="text-off-white/60 whitespace-pre-wrap"></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6">
            <button id="download-link"
              class="bg-carbon-navy font-semibold text-sm border border-white/20 px-4 py-2 inline-block hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">
              Download Artifact
            </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ERROR SECTION -->
      <div id="error-section" class="mt-6 border border-red-400/30 p-6 text-sm hidden max-w-4xl">
        <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold mb-2">Upload Failed</p>
        <p class="text-red-400/80 mb-4">
          We found issues with your file — see details below
        </p>
        <ul id="error-list" class="space-y-4 text-off-white/70"></ul>
      </div>

      <!-- FILE REQUIREMENTS -->
      <details class="mt-6 text-off-white/70">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer">View File Requirements</summary>

        <div class="mt-4 space-y-6 text-off-white/60">

          <div>
            <strong class="text-off-white/80">Required Fields</strong>
            <p class="mt-2">
              For demonstration purposes, the system expects a minimal set of fields that define an event:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 font-mono text-off-white/50">
              <li>timestamp</li>
              <li>stream_id</li>
              <li>event_type</li>
              <li>actor</li>
              <li>object</li>
              <li>notes</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
              These fields capture the essentials needed to reconstruct a reliable event sequence:
              when something happened, what occurred, and what it affected.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Column order does not matter. All required fields must be present.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <strong class="text-off-white/80">Format Notes</strong>
            <p class="mt-2">
              This example uses a simplified input format to keep the reconstruction process clear
              and predictable.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2">
              In real deployments, data can include additional fields and more complex structures.
              Those are mapped into the system during integration.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <strong class="text-off-white/80">Timestamp Requirements</strong>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Timestamps must be ISO 8601 with timezone.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-1">
              Example: <code class="text-off-white/50">2024-01-01T10:00:00Z</code>
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </details>

      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-off-white/80">
        <p>
          Prima Veritas does not modify or infer missing data. Inputs must match the required
          format to ensure reproducible results.
        </p>
        <p>
          Do not upload sensitive or personal data. Files are processed for demonstration purposes only.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
  <div id="download-modal" class="fixed inset-0 bg-black/70 flex items-center justify-center z-50 hidden">
    <div class="bg-charcoal border border-white/10 p-8 max-w-md w-full mx-4">
      <h2 class="text-off-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">Download Artifact</h2>
      <p class="text-off-white/60 text-sm mb-6">
        Enter your email to download your artifact.<br/>
        We do not retain your uploaded data.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <label class="text-off-white/60 text-xs block mb-1">Email <span class="text-red-400">*</span></label>
          <input id="modal-email" type="email" placeholder="you@example.com"
            class="w-full bg-carbon-navy border border-white/10 text-off-white text-sm px-3 py-2 focus:outline-none focus:border-white/30" />
          <p id="modal-email-error" class="text-red-400 text-xs mt-1 hidden">Email is required.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="text-off-white/60 text-xs block mb-1">Company <span class="text-off-white/30">(optional)</span></label>
          <input id="modal-company" type="text" placeholder="Acme Corp"
            class="w-full bg-carbon-navy border border-white/10 text-off-white text-sm px-3 py-2 focus:outline-none focus:border-white/30" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex gap-3">
        <button id="modal-submit"
          class="bg-carbon-navy font-semibold text-sm border border-white/20 px-4 py-2 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">
          Download Artifact
        </button>
        <button id="modal-cancel"
          class="text-sm text-off-white/40 hover:text-off-white/70 transition-colors px-2">
          Cancel
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


  <script>
const fileInput = document.querySelector('input[type="file"]');
const button = document.getElementById("generate-btn");
const statusEl = document.getElementById("status-message");

let fileSelected = false;
let artifactGenerated = false;
let pendingDownloadUrl = null;
let userEmail = "";
let userCompany = "";

fileInput.addEventListener("change", () => {
  fileSelected = true;
  artifactGenerated = false;

  const file = fileInput.files[0];
  statusEl.textContent = file ? file.name : "";
  statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-red-400");
  statusEl.classList.add("text-off-white/60");

  button.disabled = false;
  document.getElementById("btn-text").textContent = "Generate Artifact";
  document.getElementById("btn-spinner").classList.add("hidden");
  document.getElementById("error-section").classList.add("hidden");
  document.getElementById("error-list").innerHTML = "";
});

button.addEventListener("click", async () => {
  const file = fileInput.files[0];

  if (!fileSelected || !file || artifactGenerated) {
    statusEl.textContent = "No file selected.";
    statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-off-white/60");
    statusEl.classList.add("text-red-400");
    return;
  }

  button.disabled = true;
  document.getElementById("btn-spinner").classList.remove("hidden");

  try {
    const formData = new FormData();
    formData.append("file", file);

    const res = await fetch("https://api.primaveritas.io/artifact", {
      method: "POST",
      body: formData
    });

    const raw = await res.json();

    if (!res.ok || raw.status === "error") {
      if (Array.isArray(raw.errors)) {
        const errorSection = document.getElementById("error-section");
        const errorList = document.getElementById("error-list");

        const friendlyMessage = (reason) => {
          switch (reason) {
            case "no_file_uploaded":         return "Please upload a CSV file.";
            case "missing_required_columns": return "Your CSV is missing required columns.";
            case "invalid_format":           return "Invalid format.";
            case "column_count_mismatch":    return "CSV structure is incorrect.";
            case "internal_server_error":    return "Unexpected error. Please try again.";
            default:                         return reason || "Unexpected error. Please try again.";
          }
        };

        errorList.innerHTML = raw.errors.map(e => {
          let label = e.row
            ? "Row " + e.row + (e.field ? " — " + e.field + ":" : ":")
            : "Header issue:";
          let message = friendlyMessage(e.reason);
          let detailHtml = "";
          if (e.details?.expected && e.details?.received) {
            detailHtml = `
              <div class="mt-2 font-mono text-off-white/50 space-y-1">
                <div>Expected: ${e.details.expected}</div>
                <div>Received: ${e.details.received}</div>
              </div>`;
          }
          return `<li class="space-y-1">
            <div class="text-off-white/80"><span class="text-off-white/50">${label}</span> ${message}</div>
            ${detailHtml}
          </li>`;
        }).join("");

        errorList.innerHTML += `<li class="mt-4 text-off-white/40">Tip: CSV must match exact column names.</li>`;
        errorSection.classList.remove("hidden");
      } else {
        statusEl.textContent = "Unknown error";
        statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-off-white/60");
        statusEl.classList.add("text-red-400");
      }
      return;
    }

    const hashEl = document.getElementById("artifact-hash");
    if (typeof raw.artifact_hash === "string" && raw.artifact_hash.length > 0) {
      hashEl.textContent = raw.artifact_hash;
    } else {
      hashEl.textContent = "Hash unavailable";
      hashEl.classList.add("text-off-white/50");
    }

    document.getElementById("event-count").textContent = raw.event_count;

    pendingDownloadUrl = raw.download_url
      ? "https://api.primaveritas.io" + raw.download_url
      : "https://api.primaveritas.io/download/bundle.zip";

    const previewSection = document.getElementById("preview-section");
    const previewContent = document.getElementById("preview-content");
    if (Array.isArray(raw.preview) && raw.preview.length > 0) {
      previewContent.textContent = raw.preview.slice(0, 10).join("\n");
      previewSection.classList.remove("hidden");
    } else {
      previewContent.textContent = "Preview not available.";
      previewSection.classList.remove("hidden");
    }

    document.getElementById("result").classList.remove("hidden");
    artifactGenerated = true;

  } catch (err) {
    statusEl.textContent = "Network or server error";
    statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-off-white/60");
    statusEl.classList.add("text-red-400");
  } finally {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 400));
    button.disabled = false;
    document.getElementById("btn-text").textContent = "Generate Artifact";
    document.getElementById("btn-spinner").classList.add("hidden");
  }
});

// Download button opens modal
document.getElementById("download-link").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  document.getElementById("modal-email").value = userEmail;
  document.getElementById("modal-company").value = userCompany;
  document.getElementById("modal-email-error").classList.add("hidden");
  document.getElementById("download-modal").classList.remove("hidden");
});

// Cancel closes modal
document.getElementById("modal-cancel").addEventListener("click", () => {
  document.getElementById("download-modal").classList.add("hidden");
});

// Click outside modal to close
document.getElementById("download-modal").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
  if (e.target === document.getElementById("download-modal")) {
    document.getElementById("download-modal").classList.add("hidden");
  }
});

// Submit modal
document.getElementById("modal-submit").addEventListener("click", () => {
  const emailInput = document.getElementById("modal-email");
  const emailError = document.getElementById("modal-email-error");

  if (!emailInput.value.trim()) {
    emailError.classList.remove("hidden");
    return;
  }

  userEmail = emailInput.value.trim();
  userCompany = document.getElementById("modal-company").value.trim();

  document.getElementById("download-modal").classList.add("hidden");

  if (pendingDownloadUrl) {
    const artifactHash = document.getElementById("artifact-hash").textContent;
    const eventCount = parseInt(document.getElementById("event-count").textContent);

    const url = pendingDownloadUrl;

    fetch("https://data.primaveritas.io/log-download", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        email: userEmail,
        company: userCompany,
        artifact_hash: artifactHash,
        event_count: eventCount,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
      })
    })
    .catch(() => {})
    .finally(() => {
      window.location.href = url;
    });
  }
});
  </script>

</main>

</Layout>